article.headline: Manhattan 88, Iona 69
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Luis Flores scored 27 points and Manhattan cruised past Iona 88-69 on Friday night for its fifth consecutive victory. Dave Holmes added 16 points and Peter Mulligan 11 for the Jaspers (18-4, 13-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who lead the league by 2{ games over St. Peter's. Steve Burtt scored 17 points, and Greg Jenkins and Tony Bruin added 11 apiece for the Gaels (7-15, 5-8). Iona played without leading scorer DeShaun Williams (14.8 points per game), who was suspended "indefinitely" earlier in the day for "failing to attend to academic- and athletic-related issues." Flores scored 14 points and Holmes 12 as Manhattan, which never trailed, raced to a 46-26 lead at halftime. Mike Konovelchick's 3-pointer extended the margin to 57-31 with 14:25 left. Burtt's 3-pointer cut the deficit to 65-47 with 7:57 to go, but Manhattan maintained its cushion the rest of the way. The Jaspers shot 57 percent from the field and held the Gaels to 43 percent.
